Source: mini-buildd
Section: non-free/devel
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Stephan Suerken <stephan.suerken@1und1.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), man-db (>= 2.5.1), po-debconf
Standards-Version: 3.8.0

Package: mini-buildd-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, adduser, mailx, apache2-mpm-worker | httpd, openssh-client, gnupg, wget, sbuild (>= 0.57.7)
Description: Minimal Debian buildd (common)
 Mini-buildd lets a bunch of existing standard and Debian specific
 tools work together to build a easy-to-setup autobuilder network.
 .
 This package includes common parts for -rep (repostitory) and -bld
 (builder) installations.

Package: mini-buildd-rep
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, mini-buildd-common, python, mini-dinstall (>> 0.6.24), cron, procps
Recommends: logrotate, dwww
Description: Minimal Debian buildd (repository)
 Mini-buildd lets a bunch of existing standard and Debian specific
 tools work together to build a easy-to-setup autobuilder network.
 .
 Install this package on the machine that should hold the autobuilder
 network's repository.

Package: mini-buildd-bld
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, mini-buildd-common, lvm2, debootstrap, schroot, dput
Recommends: logrotate
Description: Minimal Debian buildd (builder)
 Mini-buildd lets a bunch of existing standard and Debian specific
 tools work together to build a easy-to-setup autobuilder network.
 .
 Install this package on any machine that should act as a builder for
 a specific architecture.
